The paper discusses a method for planning and controlling quality assurance activities in software development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The method involves combining measurement data and expert knowledge, which could also be relevant to the software design (cs.SD) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using machine learning techniques to evaluate the effectiveness of the method, which could relate to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
